  <description type="morphology">Stems  erect; scales brown, linear-lanceolate, margins dentate.  Petiole  30--60 cm.  Blade  ovate, 2-pinnate to 2-pinnate-pinnatifid, 50--100 × 15--50 cm, base ± narrowed, apex abruptly acuminate.  Pinnae  1-pinnate to 1-pinnate-pinnatifid.  Pinnules  oblong, base ± truncate, ± auriculate, apex acuminate, incised or lobed halfway to costule.  Veins  pinnate, anastomosing.  Sori  elongate, single or double, indusiate; indusia vaulted, thin, erose. 2 n  = 82.</description>
